ingful and accessible\nresources in their communities.","index":"00262","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Will the minister commit to support Bill 213 today?","index":"00263","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Ekosi.","index":"00264","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mrs. Stefanson:</b> <span style=\"color:black\">What I will say is that,\nmore important than just reporting, is obviously ensuring that those\nindividuals get the health-care services that they need, and we are committed\nto doing that, Madam Speaker.</span>","index":"00265","speaker":"Heather Stefanson"},{"html":"<span style=\"color:black\">����� What I will also say is that members opposite know\nthat they have the opportunity to designate certain bills within the Chamber to\ncome forward for a vote, and I would encourage the member opposite to ensure\nthat this is one of those. </span>","index":"00266","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDougald </b><b><a name=\"_Toc66136726\">Lamont</a></b><b>�(St.\nBoniface):</b> Early-childhood educators are a critical part of the economic\nrecovery. They've been called essential in the pandemic but, unfortunately,\nhave been treated as disposable. Most families can only make ends meet if both\npartners are working, and without child care, they will not be able to work and\npay the bills. ","index":"00267","speaker":"Dougald Lamont"},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(14:30)","index":"00268","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Now, while this government does blame the NDP for their ideological\napproach, it's important to recog�nize there was no universal, affordable,\nquality care under the previous government, and there won't be under this one. ","index":"00269","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Why is\nthis government doubling down on the NDP's failures on child care? ","index":"00270","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nRochelle </b><b><a name=\"_Toc66136727\">Squires</a></b><b>�(Minister of Families):</b> Our government prioritizes child care.\nThat is why we invested $181&nbsp;million in the child-care system this year,\nwhich is $20&nbsp;million more than the NDP ever invested. ","index":"00271","speaker":"Rochelle Squires"},{"html":"����� Since forming government, we've also created 2,500 new spaces\nthrough our capital program. In fact, that capital program is going to create\n795 new spaces this year. And our temporary child-care grant for home-based\ncentres created 130 spaces this year at a time when we know Manitoba families\nneeded it the most. ","index":"00272","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Our\ngovernment is committed to creating a child-care system that is accessible for\nall families in the province of Manitoba. I just wish the Liberal member would\nget on board. ","index":"00273","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable member for St.&nbsp;Boniface, on a supplementary\nquestion. ","index":"00274","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Lamont:</b> I would like to share the words of a child-care worker\nand advocate. ","index":"00275","speaker":"Dougald Lamont"},{"html":"����� Quote: I look up long-term-care homes and what has come to light\nregarding private, for-profit care homes. We see lower quality in private care,\nwe see understaffing, unsafe practices, lower wages and burnt-out, higher\nrotation of staff because quality is not a priority in private programs. End\nquote. ","index":"00276","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This should be a public service, like education. ","index":"00277","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Why\nhas this government kept ECE in the Department of Families instead of under\nEducation, where it clearly belongs? ","index":"00278","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Squires:</b> I'm pleased to have an opportunity to put some more\nwords on the record about what our government is doing to ensure that we've got\na strong child-care sector in the province of Manitoba. ","index":"00279","speaker":"Rochelle Squires"},{"html":"����� We've also invested another $9&nbsp;million, for a total of\n$11.5&nbsp;million, in a new Child Care Sustainab